Senator Binos Dauda representing Adamawa south senatorial district has said that the result from his sample submitted to the NCDC tested negative for coronavirus (Covid-19). Dauda made the confirmation Wednesday in Yola, after a period of 14-days self-isolation as directed by the leadership of the Senate. He said, “I submitted myself again to NCDC for examination after 14 days in isolation and was tested negative for COVID-19. “The NCDC has seen no need to conduct further tests and subsequently has relieved me of all apprehensions. “During isolation, I did not stay in, or visit any hotel.” The lawmaker added he had no prior contact with anyone that had tested positive before and after the isolation. He noted that the isolation was in his best interest, family, friends and community even before the NCDC advised self isolation. He urged mischief maker to have rethink over peddling baseless rumor against his status and personality, the lawmaker maintained. 